# `bake` pipeline

When a schema-driven feature changes, trace it through schema loading, validation, template DTOs, proto generation, Go generation, JS generation, and any affected templates.

If a new field, target, branch, helper, import, or generated method is added in one target, check the parallel Go, JS, proto, and template paths for the same behavior.

Prefer focused regression tests that inspect generated output for emitted names, imports, helper functions, method shapes, tags, and format strings; do not rely only on helper-level logic tests.

Be careful with nested formatting in generators: code that emits `fmt` strings or TS/Go source can need a different level of escaping than normal application code.

After schema or codegen changes that affect bake output, verify `go build ./cmd/golem-bake` and targeted generator tests. For cross-target changes, confirm both Go and JS generated outputs still compile.
